# 3. 一番ドキドキする歌

Kohane: .....
Kohane: (That girl today was so cool. People who are working hard to achieve their dreams really do have a glow to them.)
Kohane: I've never heard that song she was singing before. I wonder if I could find a video or something online.
Kohane: I think the chorus was something like this...
Kohane: I guess that's not really enough to go on. I should probably get started on my homework, but...
An: ♪——!
Kohane: Maybe I'll try searching just a bit longer.
???: <I found you.>
Kohane: Huh?
Kohane: My phone just!
Kohane: A Miku...hologram?
Miku: <Hello there, Kohane. I'm the Miku from your SEKAI. Nice to meet you.>
Kohane: Huh?!
Kohane: H-How do you know my name?
Miku: <Hehe. Let's talk about this in your SEKAI. You should come visit soon. Everyone is waiting.>
Kohane: Wh-What?!
Kohane: Wh-What was that all about? What did she mean, Miku from my SEKAI?
Kohane: Oh, this is it! This is the song that girl in the restaurant was singing!
Kohane: I can't believe I found it! Hehehe. I wonder if that strange Miku had something to do with it.
Kohane: Huh? The chorus is different than I remember. Did she do her own arrangement?
Kohane: Did she change this part, too?
Kohane: ～～♪　～～♪
Kohane: Hm... I think the rhythm is different, too. That girl's version sounded a lot smoother than this.
Kohane: ——♪ ——♪
Kohane: I don't know... This part sounds a little more like it, but...
Kohane: ——♪ ——♪
Minori: Hi, Kohane! You sure have been singing that a lot lately. What song is it?
Kohane: Ah! U-Um... It's this one here...
Minori: Oh, let me hear! Huh! I never pictured you as the type to listen to rap!
Kohane: I-I guess it is a little strange...that I'd listen to this...
Minori: No, I didn't mean it that way! I just didn't expect it, that's all! Have you always been into this?
Kohane: No, I just started listening to it recently. I heard someone singing in a cafe about a week ago.
Minori: In a cafe?
Kohane: Yeah. It's a place called Weekend Garage.
Kohane: I looked it up, and apparently the owner used to be a pretty famous musician. Now it's a place where local music lovers get together to sing.
Minori: Really? I didn't realize there were places like that! A cafe where you can listen to live music? Sounds fun!
Minori: Live music always sounds so much better! I think the same thing every time I go to an idol concert. It's like...you can feel the music reverberating inside you.
Kohane: Reverberating?
Kohane: (I wonder if I could feel that same sensation again if I went back and saw that girl again...)
Kohane: Am I imagining things? This place doesn't feel nearly as scary as before. Is it because it's still light out?
Kohane: And when I really look, this graffiti is amazing! This is supposed to be a kind of art, right?
Kohane: Maybe this place is all right after all.
Kohane: If I remember correctly, Weekend Garage is just around this corner.
???: .....
???: (I could have sworn I just heard someone say Weekend Garage.)
???: Oh well. I've still got a little time before I'm supposed to meet up with Akito. Might as well kill some time.
Kohane: Found it! Weekend Garage!
Kohane: .....
Kohane: (Is it really okay for me to go back in there...?)
Kohane: (I ran out on that girl last time... I probably didn't leave a very good impression...)
Kohane: .....
Kohane: No. I already made up my mind that I'd come listen to that song again!
Kohane: So... I've got to open the door!
An: Welcome! Hm?
Kohane: Ah! U-Um... I...
An: Oh! Aren't you that girl who was in here watching the other day?
Kohane: Huh?
An: I remember because it's not often we get other girls my age in here. I'm happy you decided to come back!
An: Hey, Dad! That cute girl who came in to check us out last week is back!
An's Father: Is that so? Welcome.
An: Welcome to Weekend Garage!
Kohane: !!
???: Hm? Miku, where did you get off to? You look quite pleased about something.
